children.name: \"Usage: %s [OPTION]... [-T] TARGET LINK_NAME   (1st form)\\n  or:  %s [OPTION]... TARGET                  (2nd form)\\n  or:  %s [OPTION]... TARGET... DIRECTORY     (3rd form)\\n  or:  %s [OPTION]... -t DIRECTORY TARGET...  (4th form)\\n\"

x.name: dcgettext
x.type: char *(*)(const char *domainname, const char *msgid, int category)

children.name: \"In the 1st form, create a link to TARGET with the name LINK_NAME.\\nIn the 2nd form, create a link to TARGET in the current directory.\\nIn the 3rd and 4th forms, create links to each TARGET in DIRECTORY.\\nCreate hard links by default, symbolic links with --symbolic.\\nWhen creating hard links, each TARGET must exist.  Symbolic links\\ncan hold arbitrary text; if later resolved, a relative link is\\ninterpreted in relation to its parent directory.\\n\\n\"

x.name: dcgettext
x.type: char *(*)(const char *domainname, const char *msgid, int category)

children.name: \"Mandatory arguments to long options are mandatory for short options too.\\n\"

x.name: dcgettext
x.type: char *(*)(const char *domainname, const char *msgid, int category)

children.name: \"      --backup[=CONTROL]      make a backup of each existing destination file\\n  -b                          like --backup but does not accept an argument\\n  -d, -F, --directory         allow the superuser to attempt to hard link\\n                                directories (note: will probably fail due to\\n                                system restrictions, even for the superuser)\\n  -f, --force                 remove existing destination files\\n\"

x.name: dcgettext
x.type: char *(*)(const char *domainname, const char *msgid, int category)

children.name: \"  -i, --interactive           prompt whether to remove destinations\\n  -L, --logical               make hard links to symbolic link references\\n  -n, --no-dereference        treat destination that is a symlink to a\\n                                directory as if it were a normal file\\n  -P, --physical              make hard links directly to symbolic links\\n  -s, --symbolic              make symbolic links instead of hard links\\n\"

x.name: dcgettext
x.type: char *(*)(const char *domainname, const char *msgid, int category)

children.name: \"  -S, --suffix=SUFFIX         override the usual backup suffix\\n  -t, --target-directory=DIRECTORY  specify the DIRECTORY in which to create\\n                                the links\\n  -T, --no-target-directory   treat LINK_NAME as a normal file\\n  -v, --verbose               print name of each linked file\\n\"
